OL,3,C'Hike hat-trick' hits energy customers
OL,5,FThe energy regulator OFGEM today
OL,6,Fsuggested people should now consider
OL,7,Fswitching to fixed energy deals - 4
OL,8,Fmillion people have done so. Look for
OL,9,Fdeals below the price cap, fixed for
OL,10,Fno longer than a year - and with no
OL,11,Fhigh early exit fees.
OL,13,FYou can try to lower your energy usage
OL,14,F- for example insulation to tackle any
OL,15,Fdraughts. If you are struggling to
OL,16,Fpay, talk to your energy company. They
OL,17,Fare under an obligation to help you by
OL,18,Fagreeing on a payment plan you can
OL,19,Fafford.
